# CI required on org repos and official packages

## Official packages (`packages/<name>/`)

Before merging any official package (has `PUBLISH.md` + `PKG-*`):

1. **Must exist:** `.github/workflows/ci.yml` (job name `check`)
2. Scaffold via `./scripts/li-new-package NAME --official` (copies template) or `./scripts/ensure-package-ci.sh`
3. Mirror push: `./scripts/push-official-package-repo.sh NAME` only after CI file exists

## New GitHub org repos

**Forbidden:** `gh repo create li-langverse/...` without committing `ci.yml` in the first PR.

Use package template from `scripts/templates/github-repo/ci.yml` or copy from `li-std-core` mirror.

## Branch protection

`roadmap/scripts/org-branch-protection.json` requires context **`check`** for package mirrors. After adding CI, run (human/token):

```bash
cd roadmap && ./scripts/apply-org-branch-protection.sh li-std-core ...
```

## Audit

```bash
# benchmarks checkout
python3 scripts/ensure-org-repo-ci.py
```

Do not mark a repo "official" in `official-packages.md` until `ensure-org-repo-ci.py` reports OK.
